name			uefi_wizard
version			0.1.0-1
architecture	x86_64
summary			"Finish UEFI installation of Haiku"

description		"A standalone post-install tool for Haiku on UEFI systems.

Haiku's built-in Installer writes a BIOS boot sector and never touches the
EFI System Partition. On modern UEFI-only hardware this leaves the disk
unbootable. This tool finishes the job:

  - Detects (or creates) a 256 MB FAT32 EFI System Partition
  - Tags it with the correct GPT type GUID
  - Copies haiku_loader.efi to /EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI and /EFI/Haiku/

Includes a guided GUI wizard and a haiku-uefi-setup CLI for scripted
recovery from a live USB session."

packager		"Kevin Adams <kevinadams05@gmail.com>"
vendor			"Kevin Adams"

